featureType.name: SeamapAus_NBHL_unvalidated_macroalgae
featureType.title: Seamap Australia UNVALIDATED habitat data - macroalgae extent
featureType.abstract:
The Seamap Australia UNVALIDATED habitat layer is a collection of all candidate habitat datasets considered for inclusion in the Seamap Australia National Benthic Habitat Layer (NBHL), but that have not been validated by ground-truthing seafloor observation (ie are exclusively modelled).
This layer represents all polygons in which MACROALGAE is scored as a dominant or co-dominant class, derived from the most current version of the UNVALIDATED Seamap Australia National Benthic Habitat Layer.
This contributes to the Essential Ocean Variable (EOV): Macroalgae Canopy Cover and Composition.
